I12(7) T4Discrimination by a satellite carrierK._Notwithstanding the provisions of paragraph (1), the willful or repeated secondary transmission to the public by a satellite carrier of a performance or display of a work embodied in a primary transmission made by a non-network station or a network station is actionable as an act of infringement under section 501, and is fully subject to the remedies provided by sections 502 through 506, if the satellite carrier unlawfully discriminates against a distributor.

I12(8) T4Geographic limitation on secondary transmissionsK._The statutory license created by this section shall apply only to secondary transmissions to households located in the United States.

