I80ÿ1A1302

I89. Designs not subject to protection

I11Protection under this chapter shall not be available for a design that is_

I12(1) not original;

I12(2) staple or commonplace, such as a standard geometric figure, a familiar symbol, an emblem, or a motif, or another shape, pattern, or configuration which has become standard, common, prevalent, or ordinary;

I12(3) different from a design excluded by paragraph (2) only in insignificant details or in elements which are variants commonly used in the relevant trades;

I12(4) dictated solely by a utilitarian function of the article that embodies it; or

I12(5) embodied in a useful article that was made public by the designer or owner in the United States or a foreign country more than 2 years before the date of the application for registration under this chapter.

I53(Added Pub. L. 105ÿ09304, title V, ÿ1A502, Oct. 28, 1998, 112 Stat. 2906; amended Pub. L. 106ÿ0944, ÿ1A1(f)(1), Aug. 5, 1999, 113 Stat. 222.)

