I21Section 337 of the Tariff Act of 1930, referred to in subsec. (a)(1), is classified to section 1337 of Title 19, Customs Duties.

I80ÿ1A1329

I89. Relation to design patent law

I11The issuance of a design patent under title 35, United States Code, for an original design for an article of manufacture shall terminate any protection of the original design under this chapter.

I53(Added Pub. L. 105ÿ09304, title V, ÿ1A502, Oct. 28, 1998, 112 Stat. 2916.)

I80ÿ1A1330

I89. Common law and other rights unaffected

I11Nothing in this chapter shall annul or limit_

I12(1) common law or other rights or remedies, if any, available to or held by any person with respect to a design which has not been registered under this chapter; or

I12(2) any right under the trademark laws or any right protected against unfair competition.

I53(Added Pub. L. 105ÿ09304, title V, ÿ1A502, Oct. 28, 1998, 112 Stat. 2916.)

I80ÿ1A1331

I89. Administrator; Office of the Administrator

I11In this chapter, the ``Administrator'' is the Register of Copyrights, and the ``Office of the Administrator'' and the ``Office'' refer to the Copyright Office of the Library of Congress.

I53(Added Pub. L. 105ÿ09304, title V, ÿ1A502, Oct. 28, 1998, 112 Stat. 2916.)

I80ÿ1A1332

I89. No retroactive effect

I11Protection under this chapter shall not be available for any design that has been made public under section 1310(b) before the effective date of this chapter.

I53(Added Pub. L. 105ÿ09304, title V, ÿ1A502, Oct. 28, 1998, 112 Stat. 2916.)

